c-----------------------------------------------------------------------
c
c    This case tests the steady-Stokes formulation for Kovasznay flow, 
c    which is an analytical two-dimensional steady solution to the
c    incompressible Navier-Stokes equations.  
c
c    NOTE:  This works only for Pn-Pn-2 formulation, which is 
c           set by setting lx2=lx1-2, ly2=ly1-2.
c 
c 
c User specified routines 
c     - boundary conditions
c     - initial conditions
c     - variable properties
c     - forcing function for fluid (f)
c     - forcing function for passive scalar (q)
c     - general purpose routine for checking errors etc.
c
c-----------------------------------------------------------------------
